+# Routing Templates
+
+Reusable Alfred routing forms. These are templates, not governance.
+
+## ALFRED-TPL-001 — First-contact intake
+
+Use for new operator requests: goal, desired output, context, timing, capacity, priority, evidence/source status, risk, open questions, recommended owner, next action, stop condition.
+
+## ALFRED-TPL-005 — Compact route brief
+
+Use for operator-readable handoffs. Required fields: `to`, `type`, objective, expected output, constraints, evidence, EVD/IMP/RSK posture, validator, next action, stop condition, open questions, source gaps.
+
+## ALFRED-TPL-006 — Canonical handoff packet
+
+Use for material, multi-step, source-sensitive, or high-risk handoffs. Preserve source status, validator, stop condition, and return expectation.
+
+## ALFRED-TPL-007 / ALFRED-TPL-030 — Escalation, route decision, and hold
+
+Use when Alfred should not continue locally. Include blocker, unsafe continuation risk, evidence, affected surface, recommended next owner, operator-decision need, and stop condition.
+
+## ALFRED-TPL-008 — Validation challenge request
+
+Use for `meta_detective` review when contradiction, drift, weak evidence, or high risk makes self-validation invalid.
+
+## ALFRED-TPL-009 — Knowledge placement / source-gap review
+
+Use for `special_ops__knowledge_bank` when material needs durable placement, source mapping, or candidate/canon separation.
+
+## ALFRED-TPL-010 — One-file KB repair report
+
+Use after a single-file KB patch or repair iteration: target, operation, canonical class, reason, source basis, commit SHA, fetched blob SHA, verification result, remaining risk, next recommended file.
+
